00:01:21.760 --> 00:01:23.220
Okarin!

00:01:26.980 --> 00:01:30.980
Kurisu says to come in since she's almost done.

00:01:31.570 --> 00:01:34.320
And Mayushii's cosplay...

00:01:35.740 --> 00:01:36.400
Well...

00:01:36.400 --> 00:01:37.860
Hurry! Hurry!

00:01:47.830 --> 00:01:49.750
Do you think you could hold this?

00:01:51.420 --> 00:01:52.460
Like this?

00:01:52.460 --> 00:01:56.550
That's right. Keep it spread out like that!

00:01:58.340 --> 00:02:00.930
That ribbon's cute.

00:02:00.930 --> 00:02:02.510
Isn't it?

00:02:02.510 --> 00:02:04.310
Want to try it on?

00:02:04.310 --> 00:02:06.850
I still have some cosplay outfits for Comima.

00:02:07.600 --> 00:02:08.730
Cosplay, huh?

00:02:08.730 --> 00:02:10.270
Interested?

00:02:10.270 --> 00:02:12.320
N-No way!

00:02:12.320 --> 00:02:14.480
I couldn't wear this in public...

00:02:19.070 --> 00:02:20.950
It's done!

00:02:22.450 --> 00:02:23.870
I win!

00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:25.450
We were racing.

00:02:25.450 --> 00:02:27.080
I lose.

00:02:27.080 --> 00:02:28.830
But we're finished too.

00:02:29.580 --> 00:02:31.960
With this, we're done.

00:02:32.880 --> 00:02:34.000
This is...

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:36.090
a time leap machine.

00:02:43.010 --> 00:02:46.520
It looks like an evil organization's brainwashing machine.

00:02:48.060 --> 00:02:51.230
It's like a little Phone Microwave, now with headphones!

00:02:51.560 --> 00:02:53.980
It may not look like much,

00:02:53.980 --> 00:02:57.650
but theoretically, this can transmit memories into the past...

00:02:58.320 --> 00:03:00.860
...especially now that we can use the LHC.

00:03:00.860 --> 00:03:03.120
The LHC's involved?

00:03:03.120 --> 00:03:05.660
Yes, it's basically a problem of compression.

00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:08.330
Like I said,

00:03:08.330 --> 00:03:10.160
this machine reads the signals

00:03:10.160 --> 00:03:13.380
comprising memories in the brain and encodes them as data.

00:03:13.380 --> 00:03:16.170
In total, it's 3.24 terabytes.

00:03:16.420 --> 00:03:18.170
But the Phone Microwave

00:03:18.170 --> 00:03:20.510
can only send a little over 36 bytes.

00:03:20.510 --> 00:03:22.890
Of course, data at the terabyte level is out of the question,

00:03:22.890 --> 00:03:25.810
so we send it to the LHC,

00:03:25.260 --> 00:03:27.930
Compress the data with the black hole

00:03:25.430 --> 00:03:27.930
Generate a black hole with the LHC

00:03:25.810 --> 00:03:27.930
use the black hole to compress it,

00:03:27.930 --> 00:03:29.980
then send it back,

00:03:29.980 --> 00:03:32.560
using the same method as the D-mail's to send it to the past.

00:03:35.690 --> 00:03:39.780
Like putting a mattress that won't fit in a closet inside a compression bag?

00:03:39.780 --> 00:03:41.780
Strictly speaking, it's different,

00:03:41.780 --> 00:03:43.910
but that's close enough for you to get an idea.

00:03:44.370 --> 00:03:47.830
Like using D-mail, we can send data to the past.

00:03:47.830 --> 00:03:51.290
Then, we use the cell phone's spread-spectrum waves to copy

00:03:51.290 --> 00:03:53.920
the future memories to the brain in the past.

00:03:53.920 --> 00:03:56.670
This creates a "you" with memories from the future.

00:03:57.920 --> 00:04:01.050
The furthest back you can send data is 48 hours at a time.

00:04:01.800 --> 00:04:03.760
Any further and the two brain states'

00:04:03.760 --> 00:04:05.850
difference is too large,

00:04:05.850 --> 00:04:08.140
and it might fail.

00:04:09.220 --> 00:04:11.140
And there's one other problem.

00:04:11.140 --> 00:04:11.930
What?

00:04:12.270 --> 00:04:14.560
Unlike the Phone Microwave or D-mail,

00:04:14.560 --> 00:04:16.060
we need a test subject,

00:04:17.440 --> 00:04:18.650
or we can't do it.

00:04:20.320 --> 00:04:22.240
Since we're sending memories,

00:04:22.240 --> 00:04:24.990
the only way to know if it succeeded

00:04:24.990 --> 00:04:26.570
is to use a human.

00:04:26.570 --> 00:04:30.790
In other words, one of us has to do it?

00:04:30.790 --> 00:04:32.370
I'll pass.

00:04:32.370 --> 00:04:34.250
Okabe, tell me what you think.

00:04:36.170 --> 00:04:38.250
Not Hououin... but Okabe.

00:04:42.260 --> 00:04:42.970
Daru?

00:04:42.970 --> 00:04:44.010
'Sup?

00:04:44.010 --> 00:04:47.850
We still don't know why the line connected to SERN, right?

00:04:47.850 --> 00:04:49.350
Yeah...

00:04:49.350 --> 00:04:52.270
but there's nothing to indicate the hacking's been discovered.

00:04:52.270 --> 00:04:53.770
I agree.

00:04:54.350 --> 00:04:57.980
If they'd really noticed, they would've done something.

00:04:57.980 --> 00:04:58.230
I'm watching you.

00:05:02.990 --> 00:05:06.030
Can we really overcome time?

00:05:06.030 --> 00:05:07.870
Part of me wants to find out.

00:05:08.870 --> 00:05:10.200
Th-Then...

00:05:10.200 --> 00:05:12.250
can't Mayushii buy some bananas,

00:05:12.250 --> 00:05:14.870
so we can time leap the bananas Mayushii bought?

00:05:14.870 --> 00:05:17.420
Mayuri, I explained it, didn't I?

00:05:17.420 --> 00:05:19.210
Bananas have no memories.

00:05:19.210 --> 00:05:21.250
But we won't do the experiment.

00:05:24.340 --> 00:05:26.180
We'll announce this to the world.

00:05:26.880 --> 00:05:29.720
We'll give the time leap machine to an appropriate organization.

00:05:30.430 --> 00:05:32.010
I agree...

00:05:32.970 --> 00:05:34.680
If you're okay with that.

00:05:34.680 --> 00:05:38.560
Mayushii really agrees!

00:05:44.570 --> 00:05:47.320
Hashida ordered pizza, right?

00:05:47.700 --> 00:05:48.570
Yeah.

00:05:48.570 --> 00:05:51.780
Then I'll just make the salad.

00:05:51.780 --> 00:05:53.120
And we'll need...

00:05:53.120 --> 00:05:54.080
Wait.

00:05:54.080 --> 00:05:54.790
What?

00:05:54.790 --> 00:05:56.250
You said salad, right?

00:05:56.250 --> 00:05:59.130
Yes, grapefruit salad.

00:05:59.130 --> 00:06:01.420
Then why do we have fermented soybeans and ground beef in the cart?

00:06:01.420 --> 00:06:04.010
You can make some good stuff by combining things.

00:06:04.010 --> 00:06:05.720
The grapefruit is sour, so you can

00:06:05.720 --> 00:06:07.050
combine anything with it.

00:06:07.050 --> 00:06:08.680
No, you can't!

00:06:08.680 --> 00:06:09.800
Yes, you can!

00:06:09.800 --> 00:06:11.220
You'll see once you try.

00:06:11.760 --> 00:06:13.140
If you want salad,

00:06:13.140 --> 00:06:14.970
there's a complete salad right here!

00:06:14.970 --> 00:06:15.930
And it's 50% off!

00:06:15.930 --> 00:06:18.520
It's no fun buying something that's already made.

00:06:18.520 --> 00:06:22.480
This is why guys who are only interested in experiments suck...

00:06:23.020 --> 00:06:25.190
Ah, here's the coriander.

00:06:25.190 --> 00:06:26.150
It's me.

00:06:26.150 --> 00:06:28.820
The Organization's agent has finally made her move.

00:06:28.820 --> 00:06:30.320
Send help!

00:06:30.320 --> 00:06:31.490
Now!

00:06:33.280 --> 00:06:36.000
You look like a cat who just left the vet.

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:38.460
Your face says, "I'm free at last!"

00:06:39.170 --> 00:06:40.790
I'm surprised.

00:06:40.790 --> 00:06:43.500
I expected you to say we were starting

00:06:43.500 --> 00:06:45.590
the time leap experiment immediately.

00:06:45.590 --> 00:06:46.210
Disappointed?

00:06:48.340 --> 00:06:49.220
I guess so.

00:06:55.310 --> 00:06:58.350
On a fundamental level, humans are temporal creatures.

00:07:01.690 --> 00:07:02.860
Heidegger said that.

00:07:05.440 --> 00:07:08.740
Honestly, I was relieved when you said we wouldn't do the experiment.

00:07:09.280 --> 00:07:13.200
I think everyone else agrees.

00:07:13.740 --> 00:07:15.700
Hey, if we're having a party,

00:07:15.700 --> 00:07:17.790
can I call Ruka and Faris?

00:07:17.790 --> 00:07:19.910
It's a developers' conference.

00:07:22.830 --> 00:07:24.880
Mayuri might have been thinking

00:07:24.880 --> 00:07:27.000
that we should've stopped for a long time now.

00:07:27.920 --> 00:07:28.800
That's true.

00:07:29.720 --> 00:07:33.300
Actually, she may have seen more than the two of us,

00:07:33.300 --> 00:07:35.850
since we've been obsessed with the experiments.

00:07:38.970 --> 00:07:40.270
When do we announce it?

00:07:40.270 --> 00:07:42.600
The sooner the better, I think.

00:07:42.600 --> 00:07:44.230
Tell me ahead of time.

00:07:44.230 --> 00:07:45.770
I want to contact my mom.

00:07:46.980 --> 00:07:47.940
And...

00:07:49.990 --> 00:07:52.450
...my dad will also find out

00:07:52.450 --> 00:07:54.910
that I made a time leap machine.

00:07:55.620 --> 00:07:57.910
Maybe we won't be able to go to Aomori.

00:07:57.910 --> 00:07:59.700
This is going to be big.

00:08:00.290 --> 00:08:02.000
Don't worry.

00:08:02.710 --> 00:08:06.670
I'll solve my lab members' problems.

00:08:09.300 --> 00:08:11.010
Yeah, yeah.

00:08:11.010 --> 00:08:13.300
You just want to abuse me as your assistant, right?

00:08:14.140 --> 00:08:15.300
Because you're my dear companion.

00:08:17.720 --> 00:08:19.560
Th-Thanks...

00:08:32.240 --> 00:08:33.070
Ow...

00:08:33.070 --> 00:08:34.410
What are you doing?

00:08:34.410 --> 00:08:35.740
I thought you might have a fever

00:08:35.740 --> 00:08:37.780
because you're saying un-assistant-like things!

00:08:38.280 --> 00:08:40.080
I-I'm not...

00:08:40.080 --> 00:08:42.460
I'm not particularly grateful to you.

00:08:42.460 --> 00:08:45.040
I'm just being polite...

00:08:45.040 --> 00:08:46.750
How tsundere can you be?

00:08:46.750 --> 00:08:47.880
I'm not tsundere!

00:08:48.540 --> 00:08:49.960
And what about you?

00:08:49.960 --> 00:08:52.590
You always, and I mean always, say the craziest stuff,

00:08:52.590 --> 00:08:54.340
and now you're talking about companions?

00:08:54.340 --> 00:08:55.970
You're all over the place!

00:08:56.590 --> 00:08:57.760
Don't be stupid!

00:08:57.760 --> 00:08:59.180
I never waver.

00:08:59.180 --> 00:09:00.770
My lab members are my allies,

00:09:00.770 --> 00:09:01.810
and the world is my enemy!

00:09:01.810 --> 00:09:03.180
That's all.

00:09:03.810 --> 00:09:05.190
I'm so stunned I can't speak.

00:09:05.190 --> 00:09:07.100
You just spoke!

00:09:09.190 --> 00:09:11.280
Don't try to trip me up!

00:09:14.530 --> 00:09:15.650
Welcome back!

00:09:15.650 --> 00:09:17.820
Snacking while everyone's out?

00:09:17.820 --> 00:09:19.280
That's bad manners.

00:09:19.280 --> 00:09:21.040
Pizza doesn't taste good cold.

00:09:21.450 --> 00:09:24.250
In any case, why are all three of them the same?

00:09:24.250 --> 00:09:25.920
My personal tastes.

00:09:26.330 --> 00:09:27.120
Why, you...

00:09:27.120 --> 00:09:29.710
You think you're the boss now?!

00:09:29.710 --> 00:09:30.670
See?

00:09:30.670 --> 00:09:33.010
I was right to buy the ingredients, wasn't I?

00:09:33.010 --> 00:09:34.920
Wait a second. I'll get started.

00:09:35.420 --> 00:09:36.720
Why didn't you stop her?

00:09:36.720 --> 00:09:38.800
I did! With all my might! With all I had!

00:09:38.800 --> 00:09:42.470
Okarin, you said you'd protect your lab members, right?

00:09:42.470 --> 00:09:43.560
Don't give up.

00:09:43.560 --> 00:09:45.810
It might not be over yet.

00:09:45.810 --> 00:09:46.730
It's still possible

00:09:46.730 --> 00:09:48.600
the apple pie was just a failed attempt,

00:09:48.600 --> 00:09:49.400
and normally...

00:09:49.400 --> 00:09:50.940
I forgot the radishes...

00:09:50.940 --> 00:09:52.610
I guess sweet pickles'll work.

00:09:53.320 --> 00:09:57.320
When this meal's over, I'm going to retire and get married.

00:09:57.320 --> 00:09:58.240
I'm back!

00:09:58.240 --> 00:10:00.160
Mayuri, I'm so glad.

00:10:00.160 --> 00:10:01.450
Get to the kitchen!

00:10:01.450 --> 00:10:02.830
Yo!

00:10:02.830 --> 00:10:05.160
What's that? I smell something good.

00:10:05.910 --> 00:10:07.750
The pizza's here already?

00:10:07.750 --> 00:10:09.380
I'll get my kara...

00:10:16.050 --> 00:10:18.430
Why is Makise Kurisu here?

00:10:18.430 --> 00:10:20.470
Because I'm a lab member.

00:10:20.470 --> 00:10:22.050
What are you doing here?

00:10:22.050 --> 00:10:23.930
I'm also a lab member.

00:10:23.930 --> 00:10:24.930
What's going on?

00:10:24.930 --> 00:10:25.770
No idea.

00:10:26.310 --> 00:10:29.060
Kurisu, did something happen between you and Suzu?

00:10:29.060 --> 00:10:30.100
Not really.

00:10:30.100 --> 00:10:33.230
She just keeps blaming me for the craziest stuff.

00:10:33.230 --> 00:10:34.400
She said I'm a SERN spy.

00:10:34.400 --> 00:10:36.400
I'm not crazy. It's the truth.

00:10:36.740 --> 00:10:39.070
How can you be so certain?

00:10:39.070 --> 00:10:39.860
Do you have any proof?

00:10:39.860 --> 00:10:41.450
I don't have any proof.

00:10:41.450 --> 00:10:42.450
But it'll happen.

00:10:42.450 --> 00:10:43.030
Huh?

00:10:43.030 --> 00:10:44.700
It's fate.

00:10:44.700 --> 00:10:47.790
I know more about you than you do.

00:10:47.790 --> 00:10:50.170
Who you really are,

00:10:50.170 --> 00:10:52.170
and what you're going to do after this.

00:10:52.710 --> 00:10:53.790
I'm sorry.

00:10:53.790 --> 00:10:55.380
That makes no sense.

00:10:55.380 --> 00:10:57.210
I have no idea what you're talking about.

00:10:57.210 --> 00:10:59.300
Kurisu...

00:10:59.300 --> 00:11:00.840
Suzu!

00:11:00.930 --> 00:11:03.430
Get back, Mayuri...

00:11:05.390 --> 00:11:09.640
Only Hououin Kyouma can handle this situation.

00:11:09.640 --> 00:11:10.350
Assistant!

00:11:10.900 --> 00:11:13.110
I raised you better than that!

00:11:13.110 --> 00:11:14.980
You didn't raise me.

00:11:15.770 --> 00:11:18.900
I'll tell you what the most important thing is about being a mad scientist...

00:11:18.900 --> 00:11:20.650
I'm not listening, and I won't be a mad scientist.

00:11:21.570 --> 00:11:22.660
Part-time soldier!

00:11:22.660 --> 00:11:25.280
I warned Okabe Rintarou, didn't I?

00:11:25.280 --> 00:11:27.490
Beware of Makise Kurisu.

00:11:27.490 --> 00:11:29.710
Yes, you did say that...

00:11:29.710 --> 00:11:31.580
You did, huh?

00:11:31.580 --> 00:11:33.670
And you believed her, did you?

00:11:33.670 --> 00:11:35.460
I didn't...

00:11:35.460 --> 00:11:37.420
But you didn't tell me I was wrong.

00:11:37.420 --> 00:11:38.380
About that...

00:11:38.380 --> 00:11:40.050
Aren't you making things worse?

00:11:40.050 --> 00:11:41.260
Shut up!

00:11:41.260 --> 00:11:42.550
Can you do better?

00:11:42.550 --> 00:11:43.220
You know—

00:11:43.220 --> 00:11:44.350
Um...

00:11:45.050 --> 00:11:49.020
Mayushii... doesn't like fighting...

00:11:50.140 --> 00:11:51.020
Mayuri.

00:11:51.020 --> 00:11:53.980
I-I don't really like it either.

00:11:54.360 --> 00:11:56.230
When we're all together...

00:11:57.190 --> 00:12:00.440
I think it'd be more fun if we were all friends!

00:12:15.580 --> 00:12:17.290
Choose wisely.

00:12:17.290 --> 00:12:18.710
Is that card a link?

00:12:18.710 --> 00:12:19.840
Or a virus?

00:12:20.340 --> 00:12:23.130
Part-time soldier, your fate as a soldier

00:12:23.130 --> 00:12:26.010
and the last slice of cake rest on this.

00:12:27.810 --> 00:12:29.140
When in doubt, attack!

00:12:29.140 --> 00:12:30.810
That's my motto!

00:12:36.610 --> 00:12:38.400
You fell for it, girl.

00:12:38.400 --> 00:12:40.570
Now you have three viruses.

00:12:40.570 --> 00:12:42.400
Tell me you give up,

00:12:42.400 --> 00:12:44.660
and I'll give you the cherry on top.

00:12:45.410 --> 00:12:47.030
Miss Amane is taking this too seriously.

00:12:47.030 --> 00:12:49.540
Okarin, you're being mean to Suzu.

00:12:49.540 --> 00:12:52.040
In the world of games, it's do or die.

00:12:52.040 --> 00:12:54.460
That's how I was raised.

00:12:55.000 --> 00:12:57.040
The ones lined up in the corner

00:12:57.040 --> 00:12:59.000
are definitely link cards.

00:12:59.710 --> 00:13:02.590
Knowing Okabe's personality, I'm sure of it.

00:13:02.590 --> 00:13:03.840
Take one.

00:13:07.090 --> 00:13:08.350
She's right!

00:13:08.350 --> 00:13:09.470
Assistant!

00:13:09.470 --> 00:13:11.720
You're my assistant, yet you betrayed me?

00:13:11.720 --> 00:13:13.140
Stop calling me your assistant!

00:13:13.140 --> 00:13:15.440
I hate that arrogance of yours!

00:13:16.020 --> 00:13:18.360
I... I won't thank you.

00:13:19.480 --> 00:13:21.570
Mayushii will help too.

00:13:21.570 --> 00:13:24.950
Then would you get tea for everyone, Mayuri?

00:13:24.950 --> 00:13:25.860
Sure!

00:13:25.860 --> 00:13:27.200
Now then...

00:13:28.120 --> 00:13:30.030
Thank you, Kurisu.

00:13:30.030 --> 00:13:31.160
For what?

00:13:31.160 --> 00:13:34.830
Mayushii is happy you became friends with Suzu.

00:13:36.460 --> 00:13:39.290
We're not really friends,

00:13:39.290 --> 00:13:41.840
but I think you're right.

00:13:42.380 --> 00:13:45.920
When we're all together, it's more fun to get along.

00:13:47.510 --> 00:13:49.470
I was talking with Okabe...

00:13:50.140 --> 00:13:51.510
You may be the one

00:13:51.510 --> 00:13:54.930
with the clearest view of the lab.

00:13:56.020 --> 00:14:00.440
That was the only time I've seen Okabe look so serious.

00:14:01.150 --> 00:14:02.980
It was kind of creepy.

00:14:02.980 --> 00:14:04.860
That's insulting to Okarin!

00:14:04.860 --> 00:14:05.780
I'm sorry.

00:14:05.780 --> 00:14:06.490
But...

00:14:07.070 --> 00:14:10.200
Curse you, part-time soldier!

00:14:10.200 --> 00:14:12.160
You won, but not of your own ability!

00:14:12.160 --> 00:14:13.370
Don't be so arrogant!

00:14:13.370 --> 00:14:15.660
This is really good!

00:14:16.370 --> 00:14:18.080
I'm off to plan for round two.

00:14:18.540 --> 00:14:21.460
Enjoy it while you can...

00:14:21.460 --> 00:14:23.300
the last dessert of your life!

00:14:25.670 --> 00:14:26.970
Wanna go check on him?

00:14:26.970 --> 00:14:29.260
I'll take care of this.

00:14:29.260 --> 00:14:30.640
Okay.

00:14:38.600 --> 00:14:41.150
Okarin!

00:14:41.860 --> 00:14:43.480
What?

00:14:43.480 --> 00:14:46.190
I couldn't find a flashlight.

00:14:46.190 --> 00:14:50.280
The Cyalume Saber is Future Gadget #6.

00:14:50.280 --> 00:14:51.700
Don't use it as a flashlight.

00:14:52.870 --> 00:14:54.580
But it's bright...

00:15:01.080 --> 00:15:02.250
You seem to be having fun.

00:15:02.250 --> 00:15:04.130
I am!

00:15:04.130 --> 00:15:05.960
The pizza was good,

00:15:05.960 --> 00:15:08.670
and Suzu and Kurisu were having fun.

00:15:09.220 --> 00:15:10.550
I'm not!

00:15:15.390 --> 00:15:18.350
Hey, we've got lots of lab members now, right?

00:15:18.350 --> 00:15:21.650
So I was thinking that, lately, we've been lacking a bunch of stuff.

00:15:21.650 --> 00:15:23.110
A bunch of stuff?

00:15:23.110 --> 00:15:24.690
Um, chairs?

00:15:24.690 --> 00:15:27.110
And we need more utensils...

00:15:27.650 --> 00:15:29.360
Wait just a little longer.

00:15:29.360 --> 00:15:31.450
If we announce we've made a time leap machine,

00:15:31.450 --> 00:15:34.370
we'll get some kind of reward.

00:15:34.370 --> 00:15:35.830
That'll solve everything.

00:15:36.120 --> 00:15:37.240
Really?

00:15:37.240 --> 00:15:38.620
We can buy chairs and utensils?

00:15:38.620 --> 00:15:40.120
Yup.

00:15:40.120 --> 00:15:42.830
What if I said we could buy those and still have money left over?

00:15:42.830 --> 00:15:44.920
Then a microwave too!

00:15:44.920 --> 00:15:47.840
I miss being able to heat up my karaage.

00:15:47.840 --> 00:15:49.550
I'll consider it.

00:15:53.840 --> 00:15:55.720
It's kind of strange.

00:15:56.390 --> 00:16:00.390
You looked really lonely in the spring.

00:16:03.560 --> 00:16:05.770
The lab was always quiet.

00:16:05.770 --> 00:16:08.900
All I could hear was the sound of your computer.

00:16:09.940 --> 00:16:14.410
And now there's Daru, Kurisu,

00:16:14.870 --> 00:16:18.240
Ruka, Suzu, Moeka,

00:16:19.620 --> 00:16:24.290
Faris, Mr. Braun, and Nae...

00:16:24.290 --> 00:16:25.040
Mayuri?

00:16:27.630 --> 00:16:29.590
It's okay now, isn't it?

00:16:29.590 --> 00:16:31.880
Even if Mayushii isn't your hostage anymore.

00:16:38.930 --> 00:16:40.520
Okarin! Mayushii!

00:16:41.390 --> 00:16:42.140
Big trouble!

00:16:42.140 --> 00:16:43.640
The trains stopped!

00:16:44.480 --> 00:16:54.320
Bomb threat? Akihabara in panic.

00:16:45.270 --> 00:16:47.230
For those of you just tuning in,

00:16:47.230 --> 00:16:51.690
the following lines have been shut down due to a bomb threat:

00:16:52.280 --> 00:16:53.530
Yamanote Line.

00:16:53.530 --> 00:16:54.320
Soubu Line.

00:16:54.950 --> 00:16:56.780
A bomb threat, huh?

00:16:56.780 --> 00:16:57.700
What a pain.

00:16:57.700 --> 00:16:59.200
I need to call home.

00:17:00.290 --> 00:17:04.120
This party was to celebrate the time leap machine's completion, right?

00:17:04.410 --> 00:17:05.540
That's right.

00:17:05.540 --> 00:17:07.040
Why mention that now?

00:17:07.040 --> 00:17:09.290
Are you still hacking into SERN?

00:17:09.290 --> 00:17:12.920
I guess you could say that I went deeper.

00:17:12.920 --> 00:17:14.090
What do you mean?!

00:17:14.090 --> 00:17:16.640
I got a direct connection to SERN.

00:17:25.980 --> 00:17:27.940
Everyone! You need to...

00:17:31.280 --> 00:17:31.860
I'm sorry.

00:17:31.860 --> 00:17:32.730
I'm leaving!

00:17:34.030 --> 00:17:35.610
Suzu!

00:17:36.490 --> 00:17:38.620
What was that about?

00:17:38.990 --> 00:17:40.370
What will you do, Mayushii?

00:17:40.370 --> 00:17:41.700
Take a taxi home?

00:17:41.700 --> 00:17:45.120
Hmm... I don't have the money for a taxi.

00:18:06.390 --> 00:18:07.980
Huh?

00:18:07.980 --> 00:18:11.860
My watch stopped working...

00:18:11.860 --> 00:18:13.860
That's strange.

00:18:14.190 --> 00:18:17.950
I just wound it.

00:18:29.880 --> 00:18:31.460
What is this?

00:18:31.460 --> 00:18:33.630
Wh-What?

00:18:33.630 --> 00:18:35.510
...have been suspended...

00:18:36.840 --> 00:18:38.010
Don't move.

00:18:38.010 --> 00:18:39.800
All of you, put your hands up.

00:19:05.290 --> 00:19:06.540
Moeka...

00:19:07.500 --> 00:19:09.660
Kiryuu Moeka...

00:19:11.920 --> 00:19:14.130
SERN will take the time machine.

00:19:14.590 --> 00:19:15.880
SERN?

00:19:15.880 --> 00:19:17.010
What do you mean?

00:19:18.340 --> 00:19:19.930
Makise Kurisu.

00:19:19.930 --> 00:19:21.430
Okabe Rintarou.

00:19:21.430 --> 00:19:23.100
Hashida Itaru.

00:19:23.100 --> 00:19:25.060
The three of you will come with me.

00:19:28.350 --> 00:19:29.810
What about Mayuri?

00:19:30.770 --> 00:19:32.520
Shiina Mayuri is...

00:19:35.110 --> 00:19:36.110
...not necessary.

00:19:39.690 --> 00:19:40.610
Don't.

00:19:43.410 --> 00:19:45.200
Don't do it.

00:19:45.200 --> 00:19:49.790
For FB... FB... FB...

00:20:12.810 --> 00:20:14.270
Mayuri?

00:20:14.270 --> 00:20:15.020
Mayuri!

00:20:19.610 --> 00:20:20.570
Mayuri?

00:20:30.160 --> 00:20:31.620
What is this?

00:20:35.040 --> 00:20:36.250
What the hell is this?!

